## CLIENT PORTAL (portal_new/)

### Portal stack
- Flask + SQLite (portal.db) at C:\ScanSystem_v2\portal.db
- App: portal_new/app.py (no blueprints, no auth currently)
- Templates: portal_new/templates/ (portal.html, property.html, compliance.html)
- Static: portal_new/static/ (portal.css, portal.js, logo.png)
- Compliance engine: portal_new/compliance_engine.py
- Sync bridge: sync_to_portal.py (pipeline review.json → portal.db)
- Runs at http://127.0.0.1:5000

### Portal API routes (all in portal_new/app.py)
- GET / → portal.html (property archive + client picker when no ?client=)
- GET /compliance → compliance.html
- GET /property/<id> → property.html
- GET /api/clients → list active clients
- DELETE /api/clients/<id> → remove client from portal.db only (not disk)
- GET /api/properties?client=X → property list with compliance status pills
- GET /api/properties/<id> → property detail (compliance cards, deadlines, tenant snapshot, documents with fields)
- GET /api/documents?q=&type=&status=&sort=&limit= → search/filter documents
- GET /api/documents/<source_doc_id> → single document with structured fields
- GET /api/compliance?client=X → { stats, actions, health_by_type }
- GET /api/stats → basic document counts by status/type/client
- PDFs always served via ScanStation API: GET /pdf/<client>/<doc_id> on port 8765

### Portal database schema (portal.db)
- clients: id, name, slug, contact_email, contact_phone, is_active
- document_types: id, key, label, has_expiry, expiry_field_key, is_active
- properties: id, client_id, address, postcode, notes
- tenants: id, client_id, property_id, full_name, email, phone, tenancy_start, tenancy_end
- documents: id, client_id, property_id, document_type_id, source_doc_id, doc_name, status, pdf_path, raw_image_path, full_text, quality_score, reviewed_by, reviewed_at, scanned_at, batch_date
- document_fields: id, document_id, field_key, field_label, field_value, source
- compliance_records: id, client_id, property_id, document_id, record_type, expiry_date, status, details

**CRITICAL column names — always check these:**
- document_types uses `key` and `label` (NOT slug, name, or display_name)
- properties uses `address` (NOT name)
- document_fields uses `field_key`, `field_label`, `field_value`

### Compliance engine (compliance_engine.py)
Tracks 4 document types: Gas Safety Certificate (gas_safety), EICR (eicr), EPC (epc), Deposit Protection (deposit).
Statuses: valid, expiring_soon (within 30 days), expired, missing.
Called by app.py for /api/compliance and /api/properties/<id> enrichment.

### Portal design system
- Background: #060E10 (primary), #0B1A1E (elevated/sidebar), #0F2228 (cards)
- Accent: #7AAFA6 (teal — buttons, active states, highlights)
- Status: #10B981 (valid/green), #F59E0B (expiring/amber), #EF4444 (expired/red), #64748B (missing/grey)
- Borders: rgba(122, 175, 166, 0.12) default, rgba(122, 175, 166, 0.25) hover
- Typography: DM Sans or system sans-serif

### Portal rules
- All portal PDF interactions go through ScanStation API /pdf/<client>/<doc_id> on port 8765
- Client scoping via ?client=<ClientName> on archive, compliance, and property pages
- Portal requires client selection before showing data (client picker when no ?client=)
- Don't modify server.py, auto_ocr_watch.py, scan_station.html, review_station.html, or export_client.py when working on portal tasks
- Only modify files inside portal_new/ unless explicitly told otherwise
- sync_to_portal.py runs automatically after every ReviewStation save (single-doc sync) and on export (full client sync)
- Compliance logic stays centralised in compliance_engine.py — don't re-implement status rules elsewhere